    • Constructor Detail

      • Chunk

        public Chunk(LongRange range)
        Builds a Chunk with the given range and no mapping.

        The given LongRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a LongRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the LongRange provided has a range that exceeds 2147483647L, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a Chunk cannot be built with the provided range.

      • Chunk

        public Chunk(LongRange range,
             Function<Long,T> initializer)
        Builds a Chunk with the provided LongRange. The provided initializer generates the initial value of the element for each index. The given LongRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a LongRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the LongRange provided has a range that exceeds 2147483647L, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        initializer - generates the initial value of the element for each index.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a Chunk cannot be built with the provided range.

      • Chunk

        public Chunk(LongRange range,
             Object[] a)
        Builds a Chunk with the provided LongRange and an initial mapping for each long in the object array. The provided LongRange and Object array should have the same size. An IllegalArgumentException will be thrown otherwise.

        The given LongRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a LongRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the LongRange provided has a range that exceeds 2147483647L, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        a - array with the initial mapping for every long in the provided range
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a Chunk cannot be built with the provided range and object array.

      • Chunk

        public Chunk(LongRange range,
             T t)
        Builds a Chunk with the provided LongRange with each long in the provided range mapped to object t. The given LongRange should have a strictly positive size. Giving a LongRange instance with identical lower and upper bounds will result in a IllegalArgumentException being thrown.

        If the LongRange provided has a range that exceeds 2147483647L, an IllegalArgumentException will be be thrown.

        Parameters:
        range - the range of the chunk to build
        t - initial mapping for every long in the provided range
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a Chunk cannot be built with the provided range.
